SIMPLE: interview
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interview
<hw>In"ter*view</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>entrevue</ets>, fr. <ets>entrevoir</ets> to see imperfectly, to
have a glimpse of, <ets>s'entrevoir</ets> to visit each other. See
<er>Inter-</er>, and <er>View</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A mutual sight or view; a meeting face to face;
usually, a formal or official meeting for consultation; a conference;
<as>as, the secretary had an <ex>interview</ex> with the
President</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A conversation, or questioning, for the purpose of
eliciting information for publication; the published statement so
elicited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A recent use, originating in American newspapers, but
apparently becoming general.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interview</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interview
<hw>In"ter*view</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To have an interview with;
to question or converse with, especially for the purpose of obtaining
information for publication.</def> <mark>[Recent]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>interviewee</ent>⟦br⟧
